About

Known as the keystone state, Pennsylvania is the birthplace of American independence and the iconic Philly cheesesteak!

State facts

State Bird: Ruffed Grouse State Dog: Great Dane State Tree: Eastern Hemlock
State Beverage: Milk State Insect: Firefly State Fish: Brook Trout
State Flower: Mountain Laurel State Animal: White-Tailed Deer State Firearm: Pennsylvania Long Rifle
